	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Vincennes&#44; Ind.</placeName> <date>Augt. 12. &#39;56</date></p>
				<p>Dr Sir.  I had one of your <hi rend="underline">Seriale</hi> Bills<lb/> last winter&#45;and the other day&#44; without<lb/> much reflection&#45;gave it to a friend.  I<lb/> do not remember the price&#44; but I enclose<lb/> <hi rend="underline">five dollars</hi>.  please send me two copies.<lb/> if the price is more&#44; please trust me to<lb/> send you the balance&#44; which I will<lb/> do immediately or when I send the Subscription for the occident.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Wrap up in strong paper&#44; direct<lb/> plain&#44; &#38; send by Adams Express.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Some time since I recd a copy<lb/> of <persName>Phillipeons<add>&#63;</add></persName> Development from <placeName>London</placeName>&#44;<lb/> and read it with great satisfaction.  I<lb/> should like to know how you count <persName>Dr.<lb/> P.</persName> is he orthodox or not&#63;  Count him as<lb/> you may.  I feel much that that work<lb/> can only tend to elevate the reputation of<lb/> Judaism with all Jewish men&#44; and<lb/> that it would be read by and would<lb/> benefit the American Port. Jews&#59; who like<lb/> my self have known but little of the faith</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>except its forms &#38;c&#8212;nothing of its<lb/> principle objects &#38; tendencies &#38;c.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have lately seen a statement that<lb/> the K<add>&#63;</add>ites of the <placeName>Crimea</placeName> are <add>&#63;</add>&#44; &#38;c.<lb/> The 1&#8221; edition of the Ks. in English that I have<lb/> seen <sic>a was is</sic> Travels in <placeName>Russia</placeName> &#38;c by <persName>Dr. Clark</persName><lb/> about <date>1805</date>.  We can put the book in <add>&#63;</add>.  But<lb/> only 5 or 6 have since there was a settlement<lb/> of Ks. in the neighborhood of <placeName>Bagdad</placeName>.  Who<lb/> were Jews by descent undoubtedly and if<lb/> you wish it I can give you a refrence<add>&#63;</add><lb/> to the authority&#8212;it is from Scotch Mission<lb/> any work in which I Saw it &#38; can again<lb/> send it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">On the notes in your large <add>&#63;</add> more<lb/> fall than is His <add>&#63;</add> <add>&#63;</add>&#63;</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">Very respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(7)"><hi rend="underline"><persName role="author">Saml. Judah</persName>.</hi></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
